result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason H Zastrow was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jason H Zastrow in court with attorney Jennifer L. Weber.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Parties proceed to sentencing on Cts. 1 and 2.

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 1:
- 90 days jail straight time consecutive to Ct. 2 STAYED for 18 months Probation - concurrent to Ct. 2
- Fine totaling $883.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation; alternate 18 days jail consecutive 
- Conditions of  Probation:  Submit to a formal AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling. Absolute sobriety - no alcohol/drugs for any reason.  No contact with the victim or premises where incident occurred.  DNA surcharge is waived.

Ct. 2:
- 90 days jail straight time consecutive to Ct. 1 STAYED for 18 months Probation - concurrent to Ct. 1
- Court costs totaling $243.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation; alternate 5 days jail consecutive 
- Conditions of  Probation:  Submit to a formal AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling. Absolute sobriety - no alcohol/drugs for any reason.  No contact with the victim or premises where incident occurred.  DNA surcharge is waived.
